TY  - JOUR
AU  - Levi, Yaron
AU  - Welch, Ivo
T1  - Symmetric and Asymmetric Market Betas and Downside Risk
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhz108
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 33
IS  - 6
SP  - 2772
EP  - 2795
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Our paper explores whether a symmetric plain or an asymmetric down-beta is a better hedging measure (Roy 1952; Markowitz 1959). Unlike Ang, Chen, and Xing (2006) and Lettau, Maggiori, and Weber (2014), we find that the prevailing plain market beta is the better predictor, even for crashes. It also predicts the subsequent down-beta (i.e., beta measured only on days when the stock market had declined) better than down-beta itself. Stocks with higher down-betas ex ante also do not earn higher average rates of return ex post. Thus, down-betas are useful for neither hedging nor risk-pricing purposes.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhz108
ER  - 



